.5|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/reviews-king-gizzard-the-lizard-wizard-15850|title=King Gizzard & The Lizard Wizard - 'I'm In Your Mind Fuzz'|last=Wright|first=Lisa|date=11 December 2014|website=[[NME]]|access-date=29 September 2019}}</ref>\n|rev4=''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n|rev4score=7/10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/20019-king-gizzard-the-lizard-wizard-im-in-your-mind-fuzz/|title=King Gizzard & The Lizard Wizard: I'm in Your Mind Fuzz Album Review|last=Minsker|first=Evan|date=5 December 2014|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=2 June 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''I'm In Your Mind Fuzz''''' is the fifth studio album by Australian [[psychedelic rock]] band [[King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard]]. It was released on 31 October 2014 on [[Heavenly Records]].\n\n== Music ==\nThe album has been described as [[garage rock]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/king-gizzard-the-lizard-wizard-mn0003085959/biography|title=King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard {{!}} Biography & History|last=Heaney|first=Gregory|website=[[AllMusic]]|access-date=29 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/music/king-gizzard-lizard-wizard-australia-mircotones-9192966|title=How King Gizzard and the Lizard Wizard Went from a Joke to Must-See Psych|last=Clancy|first=Kayla|date=17 April 2017|website=[[Phoenix New Times]]|access-date=29 September 2019}}</ref> and [[psychedelic rock]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/king-gizzard-and-the-lizard-wizard-polygondwanaland/|title=King Gizzard & The Lizard Wizard: Polygondwanaland Album Review|last=Corcoran|first=Nina|date=1 December 2017|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|access-date=29 September 2019|quote=exploding with the psych rock frenzy of ''Flying Microtonal Banana'' or ''I\u2019m in Your Mind Fuzz''.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1718001/album-of-the-week-cult-of-youth-final-days/franchises/album-of-the-week/|title=Album Of The Week: Cult Of Youth Final Days|last=Breihan|first=Tom|date=11 November 2014|website=[[Stereogum]]|access-date=29 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\nVinyl releases have tracks 1\u20136 on side A, and tracks 7\u201310 on side B.<ref>{{Discogs master|761067|I'm in Your Mind Fuzz|type=album}}</ref>\n{{track listing\n| all_writing  = Stu Mackenzie alone, except where otherwise noted\n| total_length = 42:05\n| title1       = I'm in Your Mind\n| writer1      = \n| length1      = 3:34\n\n| title2       = I'm Not in Your Mind\n| writer2      = \n| length2      = 2:58\n\n| title3       = Cellophane\n| writer3      = \n| length3      = 3:11\n\n| title4       = I'm in Your Mind Fuzz\n| writer4      = \n| length4      = 2:52\n\n| title5       = Empty\n| writer5      = \n| length5      = 4:11\n\n| title6       = Hot Water\n| writer6      = Mackenzie, Joey Walker\n| length6      = 3:24\n\n| title7       = Am I in Heaven?\n| writer7      = \n| length7      = 7:06\n\n| title8       = Slow Jam 1\n| writer8      = \n| length8      = 2:55\n\n| title9       = Satan Speeds Up\n| writer9      = \n| length9      = 3:39\n\n| title10      = Her and I (Slow Jam 2)\n| writer10      = \n| length10     = 8:15\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits for ''I'm in Your Mind Fuzz'' adapted from liner notes.<ref>Track listing and credits as per liner notes for ''I'm in Your Mind Fuzz'' album</ref>\n\n'''King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard'''\n* Michael Cavanagh \u2013 drums\n* Cook Craig \u2013 guitars\n* Ambrose Kenny-Smith \u2013 blues harp\n* Stu Mackenzie \u2013 vocals, guitars, keys, flute\n* Eric Moore \u2013 drums\n* Lucas Skinner \u2013 bass\n* Joey Walker \u2013 guitars, vocals\n\n'''Production'''\n* Stu Mackenzie \u2013 production, additional recording, mixing {{small|(tracks 2, 5, 6, 8-10)}}, additional mixing {{small|(tracks 1, 3, 4, 7)}}\n* Wayne Gordon \u2013 recording {{small|(tracks 1, 3, 4, 6, 7)}}\n* Paul Maybury \u2013 recording {{sma